Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
import_ilm_data(25.10)                                  import_ilm_data(25.10)

Name
       import_ilm_data

Syntax
       import_ilm_data

       [-help]

       [-cell <block_name>]

       [-incr]

       -model_type {timing | cts | si}

       [-overwrite]

       [-xtwf <xtwf_file.spef>]

       {-dir <directory_name> | -cell_view <lib> <cell> <view>}

       [-verilog <cell_name.v> [-cell_prefix <cell_prefix> -uniquify_netlist]]

       [-sdc <file_name> -timing_view <view_name>]

       [-spef <spef_file.spef> -rc_corner <RC_corner_name>]

       [-optStage <opt_stage>]

       Creates  an  ILM  directory from existing data. It can only create non-
       merged models. This command is useful in situations where an ILM is  to
       be  created through external inputs or using data from third party mod-
       els into a format that could be recognized by Innovus.

       If the data files already exist in the specified  directory,  the  tool
       stops  and generates an error message. You can overwrite existing files
       by specifying -overwrite. You can add files to the directory by  speci-
       fying -incr.

       The  command also creates a tcl script (cell_name_ILM.tcl) that you can
       source in your command file. The script contains the following command:

       specifyIlm -cell <cell_name> -dir <dir_name>

Parameters
       -cell <block_name>
              Specifies the name of the block.

       -cell_prefix <cell_prefix>
              Specifies the cell prefix.

       -cell_view <lib cell view>
              Specifies the library name, cell name, and view name in the Ope-
              nAccess database format.

       -dir <dir_name>
              Stores the ILM data in the specified directory: the absolute di-
              rectory path or the path relative to the current directory.

       -incr  Lets you add files in addition to the existing files to the  di-
              rectory.

       -model_type {timing | cts | si}
              Specifies the type of ILM model, i.e timing, cts or si,.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each import_ilm_data parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man import_ilm_data.

       -optStage
              Specifies the optimization stage, preCTS or postCTS.

       -overwrite
              Overwrites existing files in the directory.

       -rc_corner <RC_corner_name>
              Specifies the RC corner name for MMMC  analysis.  It  identifies
              the specified corner to be used with -spef.

       -sdc <file_name>
              Specifies  an existing .sdc file that you want to include in the
              directory. It identifies the sdc file to be used with the speci-
              fied view.

       -spef <spef_name>.spef
              Specifies an existing .spef file that you want to include in the
              directory. It identifies the spef file to be used with the spec-
              ified corner.

       -timing_view <view_name>
              Specifies the view name for the ILM module.  It  identifies  the
              specified view to be used with -sdc.

       -uniquify_netlist
              Uniquifies  the  input  Verilog netlist. This ensures that there
              are no errors when ILMs are being loaded.

              Using this parameter, each sub-module for an ILM  has  a  unique
              name, which is composed of the time stamp and its original name.

              For example, in top_sm WedJun31138212009$data_path, top_sm spec-
              ifies the top-level design, WedJun31138212009 specifies the time
              stamp, and $data_path specifies the original module name.

              Default: Off

       -verilog <netlist_name>.v
              Specifies  the  verilog file you want to include in the ILM data
              directory.

       -xtwf <xtwf_file.spef>
              Specifies the .xtwf file that you want to include in the  direc-
              tory.

Examples
              *

                The following commands create two module directories:

                import_ilm_data  -cell blk1 -dir A -model_type timing -verilog
                V1.v -spef  1.spef  -rc_corner  corner1  -sdc  sdcfile1  -tim-
                ing_view view1

                import_ilm_data -cell blk2 -dir A -model_type si -verilog V2.v
                -spef  2.spef  -rc_corner  corner2  -sdc sdcfile2 -timing_view
                view2

              *

                The command creates two tcl files in  the  current  directory.
                The blk1_ILM.tcl file contains the following command:

                specifyIlm -dir A -cell blk1

                The blk2_ILM.tcl file contains the following command:

                specifyIlm -dir A -cell blk2

Related Information
              * specifyIlm

